<title>USA: U.S. mortgage application volume fell in latest wk.</title>
<headline>U.S. mortgage application volume fell in latest wk.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>The volume of U.S. mortgage applications fell 15.1 percent in the week ended April 18, according to a Mortgage Bankers Association of America weekly survey.</p>
<p>Specifically, the volume of applications to refinance mortgages decreased 27.7 percent in the latest survey week, while applications to purchase mortgages fell 12.7 percent.</p>
<p>The seasonally adjusted refinancing index rose 0.3 percent to 286.0 from 285.1 the previous week.</p>
<p>The purchase index rose 0.7 percent to 177.6 in the latest survey from 176.3 in the previous week.  </p>
